fa98d216-9bc4-4753-a0a2-935201d7360c.1c935474-7ce8-400a-ab52-8df1d1fc6eec.description=
This operation adds a flow variable to the local context. The variable is available in the current flow and its child flows.

Inputs\:
    keyName - The name of the flow variable to add.
    myValue - The value to assign to the flow variable.

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the value of "myValue" input field.

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.

Note\:
   If a flow variable with the same name already exists, its value will be overwritten.

fa98d216-9bc4-4753-a0a2-935201d7360c.4280ec39-0244-46af-b851-cf2d9b341ffc.description=
Retrieves the requested Windows Performance Counter Value.  Takes 5 samples in 1 second intervals and returns the average.

Input Parameters\:
host - Hostname or ip address of the target machine.
object - The counter object (ex. Processor).
counter - The counter's name (ex. % Processor Time).
instance - The instance of the counter (if applicable) (ex. _Total).
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host for this operation (can be left blank).
password - Password of the user.

Responses\:
success - Retrieved the counter successfully.
failure - Failed to retrieve the counter.

Extra Results\:
VALUE - The actual value captured.

Notes\:
This operation checks the value of a performance counter that must be running on the target windows host prior to flow execution\:
Performance Object\: Processor
Performance Counter\: % Processor Time
This performance counter can be enabled using PerfMon.exe on the target host.

fa98d216-9bc4-4753-a0a2-935201d7360c.9d54a162-1f30-4baa-92f5-11da889c8377.description=
Checks if a number or word is greater than another number or word. Word comparison is case-sensitive in alphabetical order.

Inputs\:
value1 - The first value.
value2 - The second value.

Returns\:
value1 > value2

Responses\:
success - The boolean operation was evaluated to true.
failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false.
